    "body": "Code looks good and works well enough for this use case, :+1: \n\nIf this does get expanded with more use cases in the future, I feel that there should probably be some kind of state-tracking. Running more elaborate rules on every mod load would feel a bit wrong. Also, if we  eventually do add the cleanup option, and the user declines, he'd be forced into the dialog every time the mod loads.\n\nI don't really have a good idea where to keep that state, though. Maybe just storing a cookie with the mod's version in settings.yaml might be enough. Then skip migrations if that cookie matches the current version, otherwise run them. Would only work for upgrades, though, not downgrades.\n\nI could see migrations ending up needing identifiers and a flag indicating whether they are mandatory as well.\n"
  },
